<h2>{atlas} ... {/atlas}</h2>

The {atlas}-tag is used to draw various kinds of maps.

<h3>Attributes</h3>
<i>Note: All attributes are optional.</i>
<blockquote><dl>

<dt><b>bgcolor</b> = <i>color</i><dd>
          The color of the sea.

<dt><b>fgcolor</b> = <i>color</i><dd>
          The color of the solid ground.

<dt><b>width</b> = <i>width in pixels</i><dd>
          The width of the image in pixels.

<dt><b>height</b> = <i>height in pixels</i><dd>
          The height of the image in pixels.

<dt><b>region</b> = <i>region name</i><dd>
          Zoom the map to a specified region.  Regions:
          <atlas-list-regions>#name#, </atlas-list-regions>

<dt><b>help</b><dd>
          Gives this help.

</dl></blockquote>



<h2>{atlas-country}</h2>

The {atlas-country}-tag is an internal tag used inside
the {atlas}-tag.

<h3>Attributes</h3>
<blockquote><dl>

<dt><b>name</b> = <i>name of the country</i><dd>
          The name of the country.  The name is
          case insensitive.  Example: <tt>Sweden</tt>

<dt><b>domain</b> = <i>top domain name of the country</i><dd>
          The domain name of the country.  Can be used instead
          of the <b>name</b> attribute. The domain name is
          case insensitive.  Example: <tt>se</tt>

<dt><b>color</b> = <i>color</i><dd>
          The color with which the country will be painted.

</dl></blockquote>



<h2>Example 1</h2>

<blockquote>

<pre>
{atlas}
  {atlas-country name=Sweden}
  {atlas-country name=Greece}
  {atlas-country name=Brazil}
{/atlas}
</pre>

<atlas>
  <atlas-country name=Sweden>
  <atlas-country name=Greece>
  <atlas-country name=Brazil>
</atlas>

</blockquote>



<h2>Example 2</h2>

<blockquote>

<pre>
{atlas width=300 fgcolor=forestgreen bgcolor=navyblue region="South East Asia"}
  {atlas-country name=Japan color=yellow}
{/atlas}
</pre>

<atlas width=300 fgcolor=forestgreen bgcolor=navyblue region="South East Asia">
  <atlas-country name=Japan color=yellow>
</atlas>

</blockquote>



<h2>{atlas-list-regions} ... {/atlas-list-regions}</h2>

The {atlas-list-regions}-tag is an <i>output</i> tag that lists
the geographical regions.

<h3>Variables</h3>
<blockquote><dl>

<dt><b>#name#</b><dd>
          The name of a region.

</dl></blockquote>



<h2>{atlas-list-countries} ... {/atlas-list-countries}</h2>

The {atlas-list-countries}-tag is an <i>output</i> tag that lists
the countries.

<h3>Variables</h3>
<blockquote><dl>

<dt><b>#name#</b><dd>
          The name of a country.

</dl></blockquote>
